gerontophilia is a 2013 canadian romantic comedy film directed by bruce labruce and written by labruce and daniel allen cox . it was screened in the vanguard section at the 2013 toronto international film festival . described as a gay harold and maude , the film follows lake , a young man who takes a job in a nursing home and develops a romantic and sexual attraction to mr. peabody , a senior citizen resident in the facility . unlike most of labruce 's earlier films , gerontophilia is not sexually explicit ; instead , labruce chose to adapt his traditional themes of sexual taboo into a film more palatable to a mainstream audience .